","html":"<div class="rd3-page">
    <header class="header" style="background-image: url('/apps/molgenis-viz/img/home-header.jpg');">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>MOLGENIS-RD3</h1>
            <p>About the database</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-filter" />
    </header>
    <div class="section bg-gray-000">
        <div class="section-content">
            <h2 id="section-available-tables-title">About the data model</h2>
            <p>In RD3, data is stored across many tables. An overview of the main tables of interest can be found below. If you are already familiar with the data model, you can <a href="../tables/#/">view all tables</a>. All reference tables and ontologies are stored in the <a href="../../../CatalogueOntologies/tables/#/">ontologies database</a>.</p>
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th scope="col">Table</th>
                        <th scope="col">Description</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            <a href="../tables/#/Individuals">
                                Individuals
                            </a>
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            An overview of the individuals (participants, patients, etc.) that are the focus of study. This includes demographics and clinical characteristics, as well as information of the data providers and references to related records within the database.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            <a href="../tables/#/Pedigree">Pedigrees</a>
                        </td>
                        <td>Overview of families (based on PED format). The definition of family members and the relationships between them are stored in <a href="../tables/#/PedigreeMembers">Pedigree Members</a>.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            <a href="../tables/#/ClinicalObservations">Clinical Observations</a>
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            Overview table containing information on clinical findings about an individual. Further details about clincial findings can be found in the <a href="../tables/#/DiseaseHistory">Disease History</a> and <a href="../tables/#/PhenotypeObservations">Phenotype Observations</a> tables.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="../tables/#/Samples">Samples</a></td>
                        <td>Metadata on samples and their availability. There are also extensions for specific sample types.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="../tables/#/Experiments">Experiments</a></td>
                        <td>Information about the experiments that were performed.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="../tables/#/Files">Files</a></td>
                        <td>An aggregated view of files generated and where they are located. Specific locations and access information can be found in the <a href="../tables/#/FileLocations">File Locations</a> and <a href="../tables/#/FileStorageLocation">File Storage Locations</a> tables.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            <a href="../tables/#/VariantInterpretationAnalyses">
                                Variant Interpretation Analyses
                            </a>
                        </td>
                        <td>An overview of the variant interpretations performed. Further information is stored in the <a href="../tables/#/VariantInterpretations">Variant interpretations</a> and <a href="../tables/#/InterpretationConsensus">Variant Interpretation Consensus</a>. Variants are defined in the <a href="../tables/#/GenomicVariants">Genomic Variants</a> table.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>","javascript":"","dependencies":{"css":[],"javascript":[]}}

