}","html":"<div class="rd3-page">
    <header class="header" style="background-image: url('/apps/molgenis-viz/img/home-header.jpg');">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>MOLGENIS-RD3</h1>
            <p>Data submission</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-filter" />
    </header>
    <div class="section bg-gray-050">
        <div class="section-content">
            <h2>Overview of the submission process</h2>
            <p>There are three steps for submitting sample and experiment metadata to RD3. Please see our <a href="#">data submission manual</a> for further instructions on the data submission and bulk import process.</p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Register data in PhenoStore</strong></p>
                    <p>Register clinical and phenotypic metadata in PhenoStore. On a daily basis, RD3 will be retrieve the latest data from PhenoStore including new submissions and updating existing records.</p>
                    <p>If you have any issues with this step, please contact PhenoStore for support.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Enter data into one of the RD3 templates</strong></p>
                    <p>There are several templates are available for submitting data to RD3. Each template is designed for a specific samples and experiment type. Download the relevant template and enter the data that you would like to submit to RD3. Templates will have required fields and optional fields, as well as dropdown lists that contain RD3-specific values. You may import as many samples and/or experiments as you like.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Import data into RD3</strong></p>
                    <p>After completing the template, go to the <a href="#">Upload page</a>, click the "browse" button to select your file, and click the "import" button.</p>
                    <p>Once the import process has begun, a progress page will be displayed which will show the current status. If there are any errors, the import will stop and the error message will be displayed. Correct the error(s) and repeat the process until all errors are resolved.</p>
                    <div class="alert-info p-3">
                        <span><strong>Note:</strong> Data will not be imported into RD3 until all errors are resolved.</span>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section bg-gray-000">
        <div class="section-content">
            <h2>Download submission templates</h2>
            <form id="download" class="centered-form">
                <legend class="font-size-base">Which template would you like to download?</legend>
                <div class="d-flex flex-column">
                    <label for="type-select">Select a template</label>
                    <select id="type-select">
                        <option value="" selected>---Select---</option>
                        <option value="lrGS">lrGS</option>
                        <option value="OGM">OGM</option>
                        <option value="RNA">RNA</option>
                        <option value="srDNA">srDNA</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div class="mt-4">
                    <fieldset>
                        <legend class="font-size-base">Would you also like to update existing records?</legend>
                        <label>
                            <input type="radio" name="includeRecords" value="no" checked/>
                            <span>No</span>
                        </label>
                        <label>
                            <input type="radio" name="includeRecords" value="yes"/>
                            <span>Yes</span>
                        </label>
                    </fieldset>
                </div>
                <button id="download" class="btn btn-primary">
                    Download template
                </button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>","javascript":"const formElem = document.getElementById("download");
formElem.addEventListener("submit", (event) => event.preventDefault())","dependencies":{"css":[],"javascript":[]}}
